On Mon, 19 Apr 1999, Craig Whitmore wrote:
> The bios when you set up IDE drives only gives an option of 2 IDE channels..
> How can
> you set the others up? Or an I asking a stupid question?
> 
> Thanks
>
Well, Linux doesn't care what the bios has to say. This is not a stupid
question. It's just that Linux is a good enough OS to probe it's own
devices, and you don't have to put anything in your bios about them (at
least for ide devices).
